<TITLE> CA's special assistants get portfolios </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)Portfolios have been distributed among three special assistants to the chief adviser, an official said Saturday. Kazi Mostak Zahir, assistant pres secretary to the chief adviser, told bdnews24.com by telephone that retired brigadier general MA Malek Mollah was assigned to the post and telecommunications ministry. Barrister Debashish Roy was given the portfolio of Chittagong Hill Tracts affairs and Prof M Tamim will take charge of the energy and mineral resources portfolio. They were appointed special aides to the chief adviser, with the status of state minister Thursday. In a statement Saturday, the Press Information Department said the portfolios were distributed in line with the Rules of Business 1996. bdnews24.c
